This paper deals with load balancing in distributed stream processing engines, which is a problem related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of partial key grouping as a new stream partitioning scheme, which falls under the category of system design and analysis (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of network interfaces (cs.NI) and cryptography (cs.CR) in the implementation of the proposed scheme.
